parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defects in various interior components can lead to inconvenience, discomfort, and potentially hazardous situations, affecting the overall driving experience and safety.
The recurring failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to potential accidents or stranding the driver. This can also lead to costly repairs and towing.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the vehicle has to be towed
the fuel pump needs to be replaced frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water tank leaks can cause water damage, corrosion, and electrical issues, potentially leading to safety hazards and costly repairs.
False alarms from the propane gas detector can cause unnecessary panic and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The propane gas detector goes off for no reason

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel line failure can cause fuel leaks, fires, and engine stall, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
The sticking door, missing latch and lock knob, and falling shade can cause inconvenience, discomfort, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The entry door sticks at the bottom
screen door is missing latch and lock knob
shade on door assembly falls off
window day-night shades do not fold flat and come apart

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of exterior components such as the front right fender can cause damage to the vehicle, other vehicles, or pedestrians, and lead to accidents or injuries.
